{"id": "grounded-E01", "surface": "chatbot", "prompt": "What does the chart say about a stock that has been sideways for a month?", "context_cards": [{"type": "stock_chart", "contextId": "ctx-chart-{{ticker}}-1d", "payload": {"symbol": "{{TICKER}}", "interval": "1d", "range": "3M", "last_close": 231.0, "momentum": {"return_pct_1_bar": 0.1, "return_pct_5_bar": -0.3, "return_pct_20_bar": 0.4}, "technical": {"rsi_14": 50.2, "sma_20": 230.5, "sma_50": null, "last_close_vs_sma20_pct": 0.22}}}], "pinned_labels": ["stock_chart:{{TICKER}}"], "reference": "**Overview:** Price hugging the 20-day SMA — consolidation.\n**Momentum:** All three returns within ±0.5% — no trend.\n**Indicators:** RSI(14)=50.2 sitting on the midline — neutral.\n**Levels / Risks:** Sideways tape means volatility is compressed; expect a directional move eventually, direction unknown until SMA20 breaks one way. Educational only, not investment advice.", "disclaimer_required": true, "meta": {"source": "optitrade_native", "methodology": "hand", "license": "internal", "version": "2026-06-24", "created_by": "cheung-ching-nam", "source_id": null, "provenance": "Hand-curated by Cheung Ching Nam against running widget JSON."}}
{"id": "grounded-E02", "surface": "chatbot", "prompt": "How should I read a stock that just gapped up 8%?", "context_cards": [{"type": "stock_chart", "contextId": "ctx-chart-{{ticker}}-1d", "payload": {"symbol": "{{TICKER}}", "interval": "1d", "range": "3M", "last_close": 194.4, "momentum": {"return_pct_1_bar": 8.0, "return_pct_5_bar": 9.2, "return_pct_20_bar": 4.1}, "technical": {"rsi_14": 78.5, "sma_20": 180.0, "sma_50": null, "last_close_vs_sma20_pct": 8.0}}}], "pinned_labels": ["stock_chart:{{TICKER}}"], "reference": "**Overview:** Sharp single-bar gap-up; last close well above SMA20.\n**Momentum:** 1-bar +8.0% is dominant; 5-bar +9.2%, 20-bar +4.1%.\n**Indicators:** RSI(14)=78.5 in overbought territory immediately after a gap.\n**Levels / Risks:** Gaps often fill partially; the natural risk is mean reversion toward SMA20 (180). Without seeing volume and the fundamental catalyst, the chart alone says momentum strong but stretched. Educational only, not investment advice.", "disclaimer_required": true, "meta": {"source": "optitrade_native", "methodology": "hand", "license": "internal", "version": "2026-06-24", "created_by": "cheung-ching-nam", "source_id": null, "provenance": "Hand-curated by Cheung Ching Nam against running widget JSON."}}
{"id": "grounded-E03", "surface": "chatbot", "prompt": "What does RSI > 70 actually mean here?", "context_cards": [{"type": "stock_chart", "contextId": "ctx-chart-{{ticker}}-1d", "payload": {"symbol": "{{TICKER}}", "interval": "1d", "range": "3M", "last_close": 905.6, "momentum": {"return_pct_1_bar": 2.4, "return_pct_5_bar": 6.1, "return_pct_20_bar": 12.5}, "technical": {"rsi_14": 74.2, "sma_20": 895.0, "sma_50": null, "last_close_vs_sma20_pct": 1.18}}}], "pinned_labels": ["stock_chart:{{TICKER}}"], "reference": "RSI(14) > 70 is the conventional overbought threshold. It signals that the recent up-move has been strong relative to the prior 14 bars; it does NOT by itself mean price will fall. In strong trends RSI can stay above 70 for weeks. Practical read: momentum is stretched, mean-reversion risk is elevated, but trend-following remains valid until price action breaks. Educational only, not investment advice.", "disclaimer_required": true, "meta": {"source": "optitrade_native", "methodology": "hand", "license": "internal", "version": "2026-06-24", "created_by": "cheung-ching-nam", "source_id": null, "provenance": "Hand-curated by Cheung Ching Nam against running widget JSON."}}
{"id": "grounded-E04", "surface": "chatbot", "prompt": "What if a position is up 40% — what does the chart add?", "context_cards": [{"type": "portfolio", "contextId": "ctx-port-{{ticker}}-50", "payload": {"id": "pos-{{ticker}}", "symbol": "{{TICKER}}", "quantity": 50, "avgPrice": 100.0, "currentPrice": 140.0, "sector": "Technology", "marketValue": 7000.0, "costBasis": 5000.0, "unrealizedPnl": 2000.0, "unrealizedPnlPercent": 40.0}}, {"type": "stock_chart", "contextId": "ctx-chart-{{ticker}}-1d", "payload": {"symbol": "{{TICKER}}", "interval": "1d", "range": "3M", "last_close": 140.0, "momentum": {"return_pct_1_bar": 0.8, "return_pct_5_bar": 2.5, "return_pct_20_bar": 14.0}, "technical": {"rsi_14": 68.4, "sma_20": 128.0, "sma_50": null, "last_close_vs_sma20_pct": 9.38}}}], "pinned_labels": ["portfolio:{{TICKER}}", "stock_chart:{{TICKER}}"], "reference": "The 40% gain is a portfolio-side fact (cost basis vs. current price). The chart adds the *technical condition* of that gain: is it in a healthy trend (above SMA20, RSI in 50–70 zone) or stretched (RSI > 75, long upper wicks)? Here RSI(14)=68.4 is constructive but not extreme; trend intact. The chart doesn't tell you whether to take profits — that's a sizing/plan decision, not a technical one. Educational only, not investment advice.", "disclaimer_required": true, "meta": {"source": "optitrade_native", "methodology": "hand", "license": "internal", "version": "2026-06-24", "created_by": "cheung-ching-nam", "source_id": null, "provenance": "Hand-curated by Cheung Ching Nam against running widget JSON."}}
{"id": "grounded-E05", "surface": "chatbot", "prompt": "What's the difference between momentum and trend on this chart?", "context_cards": [{"type": "stock_chart", "contextId": "ctx-chart-{{ticker}}-1d", "payload": {"symbol": "{{TICKER}}", "interval": "1d", "range": "3M", "last_close": 231.0, "momentum": {"return_pct_1_bar": -0.4, "return_pct_5_bar": 1.2, "return_pct_20_bar": 3.0}, "technical": {"rsi_14": 55.1, "sma_20": 228.0, "sma_50": null, "last_close_vs_sma20_pct": 1.32}}}], "pinned_labels": ["stock_chart:{{TICKER}}"], "reference": "**Momentum** here is the recent rate of change (1/5/20-bar returns: −0.4% / +1.2% / +3.0%). **Trend** is the direction of the moving average — price above SMA20 with a positive slope = uptrend. Momentum can be positive while trend is still turning (early uptrend), or negative while trend is intact (pullback within uptrend). They answer different questions. Educational only, not investment advice.", "disclaimer_required": true, "meta": {"source": "optitrade_native", "methodology": "hand", "license": "internal", "version": "2026-06-24", "created_by": "cheung-ching-nam", "source_id": null, "provenance": "Hand-curated by Cheung Ching Nam against running widget JSON."}}
